# Test: WriteEnv works correctly in a non-interactive scripting context.
# Uses the registered "envwrite" command (see wizard_test.go TestMain).
#
# Note: testing the --non-interactive flag of Run() requires a real TTY or
# mock stdin because huh/v2 reads from stdin even in accessible mode.
# That contract is tested in unit tests (messages_test.go, wizard_validate_test.go).
# Here we validate that the envwriter produces correct output when invoked
# without any interactive prompts — the scripted / non-interactive use-case.
#
# Validates:
#   1. Multiple channel variables can be written in one invocation
#   2. Key order matches the order supplied (SLACK_BOT_TOKEN before SLACK_TEAM_ID)
#   3. The .env file exists and is non-empty

envwrite SLACK_BOT_TOKEN=xoxb-test-token,SLACK_TEAM_ID=T12345678 .env
exists .env
grep 'SLACK_BOT_TOKEN=xoxb-test-token' .env
grep 'SLACK_TEAM_ID=T12345678' .env
